issue_comments.body:
thanks for reviewing, to reproduce the issue, you can create a spark context with following jars:
accumulo-core-1.6.0.jar
accumulo-fate-1.6.0.jar
accumulo-start-1.6.0.jar
accumulo-trace-1.6.0.jar
hive-accumulo-handler-1.2.1.jar

then run some hive query like:

```
set accumulo.instance.name=instance_name;
set accumulo.zookeepers=zk_host:2181;
set accumulo.user.name=user;
set accumulo.user.pass=pass;

CREATE TABLE testtable(rowid STRING, value STRING)
STORED BY 'org.apache.hadoop.hive.accumulo.AccumuloStorageHandler'
WITH SERDEPROPERTIES('accumulo.columns.mapping' = ':rowid,colf:colq');

INSERT OVERWRITE TABLE testtable SELECT col1, col2 FROM some_hive_table;
```

then will get error `java.lang.ClassCastException` says `HiveAccumuloTableOutputFormat cannot be cast to org.apache.hadoop.hive.ql.io.HiveOutputFormat`

@dmtolpeko Hi, I created a JIRA for this problem.
The url is https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-13877
What should I do next?

